
[1]vexatious

   VEXA'TIOUS, a.

   1. Irritating; disturbing or agitating to the mind; causing disquiet;
   afflictive; as a vexatious controversy; a vexatious neighbor.

   2. Distressing; harassing; as vexatious wars.

   3. Full of trouble and disquiet.

   He leads a vexatious life.

   4. Teasing; slightly troublesome; provoking.

   A vexatious suit, in law, is one commenced for the purpose of giving
   trouble, or without cause.
